<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1023" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1023">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.00/37.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>320. Your November 11, No. 203. Department of the opinion that, relative
                            to claims presented by its instructions to Mexican Government, its
                            statement that claimants are American citizens should be accepted as
                            prima facie correct, subject to rebutting evidence by Mexican
                            authorities,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>